Struktex creates nicely Nassi-Shneiderman flow-charts, eg

+-----------------------------------+
|   WHILE i < 100                   |
|   +-------------------------------+
|   |   j := i * i                  |
|   +-------------------------------+
|   |   i := i + 1                  |
+---+-------------------------------+

The Package works OK, but has a problem regarding bold fonts in
formulae. Therefore, the original Struktex was modified.

Even if your LaTeX/TeX distrubution contains this package, you will need to
instal it in a local texmf tree. In Linux/teTeX this is typically
'$HOME/texmf'. In Windows this can be 'C:\Programme\miktex\localtexmf or
C:\Program Files\miktex\localtexmf'. 
You will need to rehash the TeX database. In Linux do a 'texconfig rehash'. In
Windows use the MiKTeX configuration tool.

If the package is available, you need to call with an option:
\usepackage[nostruktxf]{struktex}
to achieve bold mathematical symbols, with e.g. \boldsymbol

